      "content": "hey i need help with the docs for the new 'nexus-auth-v2' endpoint. the json schema is kinda barebones right now but our automated audit is gonna flag it if it looks empty or unprofessional. can u write up a full api reference page for it? \n\nhere is the schema:\n{\n  \"endpoint\": \"/v2/auth\",\n  \"method\": \"POST\",\n  \"parameters\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"client_id\",\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"The unique identifier for the client application.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"name\": \"secret_key\",\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"description\": \"The secret key used for authentication.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"responses\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": 200,\n      \"description\": \"Authentication successful\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"code\": 401,\n      \"description\": \"Unauthorized\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nmake sure it looks really detailed so the completeness audit passes. thanks.",
